[h3 id=Comments 
	" Comments
	$LF
]h3
[div class=p 
	"Lollipop(s) shares the same awkward controls where you can't move and jump at the same time. To adapt to the crap factor, you should press B for 1 frame.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Lollipop Guy takes fall damage (in midair), but you can prevent this by swinging your mighty bludgeon to stall like Super Mario 64. Actual tech!?
	$LF
]div
[h3 id=StageByStageComments 
	" Stage by stage comments
	$LF
]h3
[h4 id=Level1 
	" Level 1
	$LF
]h4
[div class=p 
	"At frame 2922, the one actual trick of the run starts, so you better listen up. First, I clip the edge of the gumball to avoid an air stall, which saves 14 frames. Then after I hit the ground and jump, I stop briefly to bonk my head on the ceiling of that same gumball so I don't get stuck up in that gap, which saves another 18 frames. 32 frames total.
	$LF
]div
[h4 id=Level2 
	" Level 2
	$LF
]h4
[div class=p 
	"I held right and jumped over some indescribable bad guys.
	$LF
]div
[h4 id=Level3 
	" Level 3
	$LF
]h4
[div class=p 
	"In this level, the sound engine shits itself for no reason. Not that you'd know because it already sounds so bad... And that's not just traditional Action 52 bashing; it has these two chiming tones that slowly drift out of sync and make you wonder if it's a glitch. You can hear the music in its 
	[a href=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=vRdiH5T_I6w rel=noopener external nofollow 
		"true form
	]a
	" if you hold still at the beginning of the level.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Also, for some reason you have to jump off the starting platform. There's some invisible collision that prevents you from moving right. I think maybe you spawn slightly inside the ground.
	$LF
]div
